channel.title: Thinking of buying an alienware computer
channel.description:
I don't know anything about alienware computers, or mostly any computer hardware stuff. More of a software guy :\
Anyway, here's what alienware wants to sell me for 1079. Think anything is wrong here?
[code] Processor: AMD® Phenom™ X4 9950 Black Edition Quad Core 2.6GHz 4 x 512KB L2 Cache Alienware P2 Chassis: Alienware® P2 Chassis with AlienIce™ 3.0 Video Cooling - Space Black AlienFX®: Alienware® Standard System Lighting - Nova Yellow Alienware P2 Chassis Upgrades: Alienware® Standard System Cooling Power Supply: Alienware® 750 Watt Multi-GPU Approved Power Supply Graphics Processor: Single 512MB NVIDIA® GeForce® GTS 250 - Superclocked Edition Memory: 2GB Dual Channel DDR2 SDRAM at 800MHz - 2 x 1024MB Motherboard: Alienware® Approved AMD® 790FX Motherboard Includes PCI-Express 2.0, BIOS Overclocking Utility, and Support for AMD Phenom Quad-Core Processors Operating System (Office software not included): Windows Vista® Home Premium with Service Pack 1 – DirectX 10 Ready! System Drive: Single Drive Configuration - 500GB SATA 3Gb/s 7,200RPM 16MB Cache Optical Drives : Single Drive Configuration - 20X Dual-Layer Burner (DVD±RW) Enthusiast Essentials: Single High Performance Gigabit Ethernet Port Sound Card: High-Definition 7.1 Performance Audio - Standard Keyboard: Standard Keyboard - Standard Keyboard Mouse: Standard Mouse - Standard Optical 3-Button Mouse with Scroll Wheel Warranty: 1-Year AlienCare Onsite Service and 24/7 Toll-Free Phone Support Alienware Extras: Alienware® Mesh Cap Alienware Extras: Alienware® Desktop Binder Alienware Extras: Owner Identification Card Alienware Extras: Internal Wire Management [/code]
Thanks guys!
